The article announces the appointments of Kurt D. DelBene, Derek Kan, and Daniel Mark Tangherlini to positions within the United States Postal Service and the Department of Veterans Affairs. Kurt D. DelBene will serve as an Assistant Secretary of Veterans Affairs (Information and Technology), replacing James Paul Gfrerer. Derek Kan will be a Governor of the United States Postal Service, replacing John McLeod Barger, with a term expiring on December 8, 2028. Daniel Mark Tangherlini will also be a Governor of the United States Postal Service, replacing Ron A. Bloom, with a term expiring on December 8, 2027.